    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, the veto power definitely seems like a huge bottleneck. but do historians see those failures as just inevitable because of how global politics works, or is there a stronger argument that the UN's very structure is fundamentally broken and needs to be replaced?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
