      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Some historians argue the failures are an inevitable byproduct of the current great power dynamics, suggesting the UN is a reflection of a flawed international system. However, a more critical school of thought contends that the institutional design itself is fundamentally broken, making reform an urgent necessity. This view advocates for significant structural overhauls, perhaps even replacing the current Security Council mechanism entirely to ensure greater global legitimacy and effectiveness.",
      "source": "target",
